        <abstract> 
<p>Suggestions and information helpful to CD in preparation for <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> voyage. David Brewster’s meteorological papers. Suggests an oyster-trawl for collecting marine animals. Recommends CD see R. E. Grant. For meteorological observations suggests F. W. Beechey’s <hi rend="italic">Voyage to the Pacific</hi> [1831] and an interview with J. F. Daniell of King’s College.</p> 
        </abstract>
